http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Call-to-address-rubber-farmers%E2%80%99-problems/article13979578.ece

The State Committee of the Youth Congress (S) has demanded that the State and the Union governments must step in to help the rubber farmers, who are in dire straits. State president of the Congress (S), Ramachandran Kadannappally, said that more than 90 per cent of the rubber production in India is in Kerala and rubber plays a big role in earning foreign exchange. However, rubber farmers are on the verge of suicide, he said.The Kerala Vikas Congress has demanded that the government should take up the burden of interest on agricultural loans. A statement issued by the Vikas Congress claimed that the policies of the UPA government had led to the steep fall in rubber prices.